== Garlic Pita Croutons ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

In a small, #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine garlic with @butter{2%tbsp}. Microwave until butter has melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Brush @whole wheat pitas{2} all over with garlic butter; cut each pita into 8 wedges. Arrange on a #baking sheet{}; season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on middle rack until chips are browned and crisp, ~{11-13%minutes}. Wash out bowl.

== Greek Salad ==

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}. Dice @roma tomato{1} into ¾-inch pieces. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces until you have 3 cups (6 cups for 4). Halve @Persian cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons.

> Keep grilling cheese in fridge until just before cooking to keep it from melting in the pan.

== Marinated Tomato & Onion ==

In #bowl{} used for garlic butter, whisk together juice from two lemon wedges, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt.

Add sliced onion and tomato; toss to coat. Set aside, stirring occasionally.

== Lemon Za'atar Grilling Cheese ==

Slice @grilling cheese{8%ounce} into four large pieces (eight pieces for 4 servings). Place @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}. Coat cheese in spice, pressing to adhere.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium high heat. Add cheese and cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per side (cook in batches if necessary).

Set aside on plate to cool slightly.

== To Serve ==

In a large bowl, combine lettuce, cucumber, and marinated onion and tomato (draining first).

Wipe out bowl used for onion and tomato; add @Greek vinaigrette{3%ounce} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Add dressing to bowl with salad; toss to coat. Crush pita chips into bite-size pieces; add to salad and toss to combine.

Slice cheese into bite-size pieces.

Divide salad between plates; top with cheese and as much lemon zest as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.